Name: Tayrona National Natural Park, Colombia
Description: It is a protected area in the Colombian northern Caribbean region. The park presents a biodiversity endemic to the area of the Sierra Nevada de Santa Marta mountain range, featuring a variety of climates (mountain climate) and geography that ranges from arid sea level to 900 meters above sea level.
